column1: 33010;instagram;2019-02-15 09:08:41;FALSE;"「女があんまり賢いと会社でも持て余すんだよ。今だってそうですよ。あなたがどれだけ、私たちを困らせているか」
たまたま女性関連の作品が続いてます😂

column2: 30年前の話かと思うとビックリな反面、現在も全然こうゆうのあるな~っと。実際に医学部入試問題とか🙃

column1: 掴みが憑依するキム・ジヨン、メインがそのキム・ジヨンを診察する精神科医のルポ調でキムジヨンの人生を辿るような感じなのですが、憑依は必要あったのか？🧐私は分かりません🤓💦💦
日本と韓国での女性蔑視は似てるけど、韓国の女性のほうがより女性蔑視に疑問を感じ行動を起こせるのかなという印象を持ちました。
けれど難しいと思うのは、どうしても妊娠できるのは女性で、おっぱいが出るのも女性で、体の構造上、また赤ちゃんや子供の成長のためにも、会社から離れる時間が必要になってくるのは女性で・・・
男性でも女性でも妊娠できるのであればもっと世の中は変わってくるだろうなぁとは思います☁️夢物語ですが😔
例えば結婚式の二次会や婚活パーティーでも合コンでも男女で会費に差があるのは当たり前。仮に同額だったら不満を感じる女性が多いのでは？というのには疑問を感じる🙁
男性＝稼ぐ、女性=家を守るという公式があるからなのか？
でも総合職でバリバリ働いている女性でもお会計を気遣ってもらうことで「女性」を感じてるコも多いような？
（所説では、女性は髪のセットやコスメ、洋服に余計にお金がかかるからお安くなっていると言われているようですが。）
けど、#metoo でもあるように、女性が性奴隷のようになるのは違うかな。
相手が嫌な気持ちになることはしたらダメってゆうだけなのだけど😏
📚 ある日突然、自分の母親や友人の人格が憑依したかのようなキム・ジヨン。誕生から学生時代、受験、就職、結婚、育児…彼女の人生を克明に振り返る中で、女性の人生に立ちはだかるものが浮かびあがる。女性が人生で出会う困難、差別を描き、絶大な共感から社会現象を巻き起こした話題作！韓国で１００万部突破！異例の大ベストセラー小説、ついに邦訳刊行。
#チョナムジュ";;en;#82年生まれキムジヨン#KIMJIYOUNGBORNIN1982

untreated mental disorder will do this to you. please. get some professional help. you don’t need to inflict pain on the people who love you. you are destined for wonderful things ❤️ you may not see column1: 33106;instagram;2019-02-15 05:18:28;TRUE;;"i am beyond proud of my dear and dope sisterfriend @samayyahdoodles !!! go support this book when it comes out and if you need illustration needs please hit her up asap!!! #repost @samayyahdoodles with @get_repost

back in october i was blessed with the opportunity to illustrate my very first children’s book! i decided to cease taking any additional orders so that i could concentrate on creating this 30+ page work of art! the book is titled “i say!” and is written by the amazing and multi-talented author vanessa vaughn jackson! this book was created to help parents
column3: and most importantly children to discuss the difficult topic of fighting against abuse and bullying. it is our hope and prayer that you will support us in #gettingthewordout about this book which will be released this spring! we worked long and hard on this project with little sleep because we wanted to get it right! please follow and support vanessa’s organization @letsgtwo to help put a stop to sexual abuse and to support survivors of sexual abuse. thank you vanessa for supporting me and for giving me this opportunity ! also thank you so much to another fellow artist and friend @blulegazy1920 for linking us together !

column1: thank you to those of you who have been supporting my work!
i love you all and hope everyone had a great night!

column1: 33151;instagram;2019-02-15 04:41:54;FALSE;"back in october i was blessed with the opportunity to illustrate my very first children’s book! i decided to cease taking any additional orders so that i could concentrate on creating this 30+ page work of art! the book is titled “i say!” and is written by the amazing and multi-talented author vanessa vaughn jackson! this book was created to help parents
column3: and most importantly children to discuss the difficult topic of fighting against abuse and bullying. it is our hope and prayer that you will support us in #gettingthewordout about this book which will be released this spring! we worked long and hard on this project with little sleep because we wanted to get it right! please follow and support vanessa’s organization @letsgtwo to help put a stop to sexual abuse and to support survivors of sexual abuse. thank you vanessa for supporting me and for giving me this opportunity ! also thank you so much to another fellow artist and friend @blulegazy1920 for linking us together !

column1: coming soon: “i say!” i say is a children's book written by n. vanessa jackson
column2: lmsw and illustrated by samayyah smith (both tuskegee alum) that was created to teach kids about the power of their voice and the importance of expressing their thoughts and feelings. i say encourages children to be confident and independent. it is a vibrant and creative approach to building positive self concept within children. i say is meant to be a conversation starter between adults and children around physical and emotional boundaries. the ultimate goal is to keep kids safe from sexual abuse through reducing risk factors.

column1: thank you to those of you who have been supporting my work!
i love you all and hope you can find inspiration to create something that can spark a change in this world 🌎 !

i put all these rules around who i could say “i love you” too. i never said it to extended family. i sometimes
column2: rarely said it to friends. and i certainly never said it to random strangers. i could say “i love your shoes
column3: ” or “i love your handbag.” but never “i love you.” that’s not to say i didn’t love my family
column5: or strangers. but the words “i love you” mean so much to me that i truly could and still can’t say them just to say it.

column1: 33281;instagram;2019-02-14 19:45:58;FALSE;"loving myself has never been so good. #valentinesday2019 🌹
i grew up with 3 brothers. no sisters. 2 of which 9 & 11 years older. they were misogynists and objectifiers of the feminine. they treated me terribly my entire childhood
column2: tweens and teens.. it’s just facts.. my oldest brother had more impact on me then my well meaning but workaholic father. so i recreated that dynamic in my relationships time & time again. last time around
column3: when explosive arguments broke out at the mention of anything #feminist or anti-rape culture
column4: i was surprised by his toxic masculinity and his toxic masculine was hurt by me calling it out.. but now after this long and nourishing silence from reflecting within relationship
column5: i’m not surprised be this story. still going strong single and relishing in every sweet second of loving myself correctly. ❤️🌹

column1: i’m so grateful for the #metoo movement as well. i remember it being such a relief to open the conversation and the channel to educate men and women about what we’ve been dealing with here for literally thousands of years.. & give voice to it. i feel it’s so far been disruptive collectively and also immensely soooo healing to awaken together ❤️ i am savouring this healing journey.
shout out to sisters (& bros) choosing to be single rn &  heal  the masculine and feminine relationship within our selves. as i heal my feminine and masculine relationship within
column2: i feel safe supported and just more authentic within myself. it’s a trip
column3: but i am basically feeling amazing right now & i hope you are too. ❤️

column1: 33361;instagram;2019-02-15 00:20:16;FALSE;"زن بودن تو کشور من با همه جای دنیا فرق داره. تو کشوری که قوانینش همگی بر علیه ما نوشته شده داشتن خیلی چیزهای اولیه آرزو به حساب میاد. علاوه بر مردم کشورهای دیگه که حتی نمیتونن یک لحظه فکر کنند که در مورد چی حرف میزنم ،  مردهای این سرزمین هم هرچقدر هم که ادعای روشنفکری بکنند نمیتونن بفهمن که زن بودن تو این کشور چه معنایی میتونه داشته باشه. ولی همه این مشکلات نه تنها ما رو ساکت نکرده بلکه ما رو شبیه یه بمب ساعتی کرده که هر لحظه امکان انفجارش هست‌ . بترسین از اون زمان که یک جرقه همه چیز و عوض کنه.

column1: i was reminded of the importance of sisterhood in the biggest way this valentine’s night.⁣
having needed to catch up on work and admin
column2: i took myself to a starbucks for an evening study session. i had my headphones in and was engrossed in my laptop. a man came and sat down opposite me and soon i became aware that he was staring at me. despite having his macbook open
column3: i could feel that he was staring at me constantly. he kept reshuffling himself and taking off his layers in an exaggerated way
column4: as though he was trying to get my attention by doing so. i messaged a friend complaining about how annoying men can be
column5: with their silent pushiness towards a woman that only she can feel and no one else sees. eventually i looked up and he was grinning at me perversely
column6: clearly thrilled that he had finally found eye contact. i took my headphone out and said “is there a problem?”. immediately
column7: he jumped out of his chair and pulled up a chair right next to me
column8: leaning into me. he said “i think your adorable and i’ve been enjoying watching you”. i said “yes you’ve been staring at me and it’s not socially acceptable”. he was shocked and baffled and asked me many times to explain what the problem was with staring at me. i said “i don’t know you”
column9: to which he said “i don’t know you either and i would like to know you”. i had to explain the basic ways in which social interaction work
column10: in the city that we are currently in (edinburgh
column12: including that when a woman is clearly busy working with their headphones in
column13: you do not try to stare them down until they feel the need to address you. he continued questioning everything i was explaining
column14: so i said i would speak to one of the staff at starbucks if he didn’t leave me alone
column15: to which he said strangely “yeah just call the police”. a member of staff was walking over past us to bring a drink to another customer
column16: so i called out to him to ask this man to stop harassing me. this man was about 7 foot tall and i thought he would help me by dealing with the issue. {continued >} ⁣

column1: i said directly to this member of staff
column2: can you ask this man to stop harassing me. he looked around awkwardly and shrugged. my harasser started mumbling about how i was making it up and saying all kinds of things. the staff member then seemed to realise that this man was clearly trying to cover his tracks
column3: and at that point he said “ok
column5: alright” and then walked away. my harasser then looked at me disappointedly and moved to sit behind me
column6: a few tables away. tears began streaming down my face because of the distress and discomfort of the situation
column7: and how i now felt exposed and unable to work
column9: having not even drunk my starbucks yet.

column1: it was at that point that two women-in-shining-heels came over from a nearby table and asked if i was ok. they were warm and caring and talked to me about what i felt like doing next to be able to continue working. a few mins later
column2: a guy who had been sitting nearby and just left
column3: came back into starbucks and came over to say that the harasser had just left too and was standing outside starbucks
column4: clearly waiting for me. the women offered to walk me to a taxi so that i didn’t have to walk past him alone as he was clearly unsafe. he started trying to speak to me as he saw me come out
column5: flanked by the two women but we passed swiftly. they told me this was what girl power was for
column6: and gave me a hug before i got in the taxi.

column1: if it hadn’t been for these two angels i would have felt distressed and scared; and having had ptsd in the past
column2: i find i am extra affected when these kinds of boundary-assaults happen. the guy who came back in to tell me the harasser was waiting outside did represent the good men out there
column3: who do act in these situations. but unfortunately
column4: as epitomised by the staff member
column5: some men just don’t seem to get it

column2: and this situation was very mild compared to many situations of sexual harassment and assault. but it matters. women deal with this stuff every single day. and if we can become eachothers women in shining heels like those women were for me
column4: that is one silver lining. • photo reposted from @dreamgaia •

column1: 33404;instagram;2019-02-14 23:53:57;FALSE;"keep the faith! let your faith be bigger than your fear. it’s all about your mindset. everything you do. everything you think. everyone you meet. all of your experiences. how you choose to interpret those experiences. everything is all about your mindset.

it’s the most important part to any person. and it’s completely under your control. it’s completely in your hands. you control what you make of the things and people and places you experience. you control what kind of day you have. you control how you interpret and react to everything that happens around you. you. not anyone else. you.

column2: we want to see god's protection as a magic force field that keeps us from all harm. yes
column3: god has to stop any evil or destruction but we must remember that we live in a fallen world where we have free will and sometimes god works in ways that we do not understand. sometimes god's protection comes in the form of peace and strength in the middle of despair. sometimes god's protection comes as an ending because he sees something more on the horizon that we cannot see. as a believer in jesus
column4: we are promised a new life covered under the protection of god in which nothing can separate us from his love. rest knowing that no matter what hardship you face
column5: god is your provider and protector

column1: 33512;instagram;2019-01-31 16:22:19;FALSE;"a song i'd written years prior as a teenager while working at rye playland ended up fitting the bill too. it was about the greek goddess demeter and her daughter persephone. this was way before al gore invented the internet
column2: so i actually had to call my friend helen to drive a couple miles out to the bar by the scattered housing off spring street—because i couldn't remember demeter's name
column3: but knew there was a bar named after her that we passed every morning on the school bus. the bar was demeter's tavern and the song is ""wintertime greys."" at this time i was listening to suzanne vega's new cassette ""solitude standing
column4: which i bought off another kid who gave out quarters at playland after he bought it but only liked ""luka"" and nothing else. there i learned what a ""case quarter"" was and also made friends with a woman who would light herself on fire and high dive into a shallow water pool right by me every shift. she was older but flirted with me

column1: since i was 18yrs old i was in one of the most toxic emotionally abusive relationships that casted a shadow over my life until i was 24yrs old. i am not one to usually talk about my personal life -due to the ridiculous shame that is tied to being in an abusive relationship
but in the spirit of the holiday i felt like i'd share some of my experiences.
1. held a knife to my throat ""jokingly""
2. shoved me hard in front of my sister.
3. broke into a house that i had gone to
column2: to escape him - then chased me around the house aggressively yelling & verbally attacking me saying ""yr a cunt

column1: 4. threw away my birth certificate while i was at school.
ex: he would tell me he loved me to get sex then leave immediately after...a quote ""how does it feel to fuck yr worse nightmare""-g.m.
emotional abuse has physical & behavioral side effects i didnt even realize why i had such as..
to all the people that are or have been in an abusive relationship it is not yr fault. abuse in any form is never yr fault!
if you’re being mentally and emotionally abused
column2: trust your instincts. know that it isn’t right and you don’t have to live this way. day by day it's important to forgive yrself & take space for yrself.

column1: 33591;instagram;2019-02-14 21:18:56;FALSE;"attorney michael avenatti said thursday that he's given prosecutors a vhs tape showing r. kelly having sex with an underage girl.
in a report published thursday afternoon
column2: cnn said they have viewed the tape
column3: noting it ""appears to show kelly having sex with a girl who refers to her body parts as 14 years old.""

column2: who's currently repping an alleged kelly whistleblower
column3: added context to the tape in a statement to the news outlet. according to avenatti
column4: his client ""knows the identity"" of both kelly and the unidentified girl seen in the tape. his client reportedly worked for kelly for decades.

column1: the ""clear and explicit"" tape is said by cnn to span nearly 43 minutes in length and shows a man
column3: engaging in multiple sexual acts with the girl (including urination) while repeatedly referring to ""14-year-old pussy.""

column1: a mole that could possibly identify the man in the video as kelly is also mentioned in the report as being visible in the newly surfaced video. kelly's own identifying mole

column1: this is a study of one of the pieces in my series that deals with violence towards women called ""it becomes us”. each painting will reflect a different woman’s individual and unique story. these stories are then translated onto life sized canvases. they are visual realizations of their own feelings
column2: and raw emotional experiences with this horrible issue. all subjects remain unidentifiable in order to highlight the universal commonality associated with violence against women.

column1: i would like to thank all the strong women who are participating in this project with me and for the courage it takes to tell and share their stories through art❤️
these particular pieces will be part of the ""breaking the silence on domestic violence"" evening of performance and visual arts at the winnipeg art gallery this friday the 23rd.
you can view the art between 11:00am and 8:30 pm. performances by the wso and others...with stories from victims
column2: families and survivors start at 6:00pm 8:30 pm.

column3: blivit undersökt samt lämnat blodprov som visat sig innehålla spår av narkotika. något som inte är ovanligt i samband med våldtäkter (som bekant drogas ofta våldtäktsoffer).

column2: trots jennys dokumenterade skador samt att hon till och med lyckas ringa 112 under pågående våldtäkt. istället blir alltså jenny åtalad för narkotikabrott.

column1: rättegången idag fick avbrytas för att ovan nämnda blodprov visade sig vara daterat till dagen efter jenny lämnade sitt blodprov. alltså är det inte säkert att det ens är jennys blod. åklagaren hade fått information om detta men hävdade att han inte hade fått det (...) så därför skjuts rättegången nu upp...
tror ni att de tänker att det blir lugnare nästa gång kanske...? inte lika mycket folk som sluter upp?

detta är ett så otroligt sjukt fall att man inte vet var man ska börja. döms jenny öppnar det upp för otroligt obehagliga saker. om en kvinna blivit drogad/är drogpåverkad och blir våldtagen kommer hon inte att kunna söka hjälp och anmäla våldtäkten utan att riskera att själv bli åtalad.

column2: detta angår oss alla. döms jenny går vi en oerhört mörk och kvinnofientlig framtid till mötes.

column1: 33903;instagram;2019-02-14 17:31:07;FALSE;i was 8 years old when i realized all i wanted was to be a musician. i never had another dream. i made happy sacrifices
column2: some not so happy. i pursued it like my life depended on it
column4: in a way it felt like it did. while people in music wring their hands about ryan adams
column5: i kindly ask you take into consideration how ridiculously commonplace behavior like his is in our industry. it happens on tour
column6: at shows. in the office or the studio. it’s disgusting and we should do better
column8: it’s a big reason why i decided to step out of the business altogether. some of you know i decided to stop touring about two years ago. maybe i’ll make more music. maybe i quit? i don’t know. i realized the person i make music for is me
column9: and if i’m not in a good space
column10: what the hell is the point? frankly i grew tired of witnessing it
column13: complicated list of other issues that plague the business. both of my #metoo experiences happened while i was on tour. at any rate—i try to keep things positive on here
column14: but i would hate to see another “dig dong the witch is dead
column15: equality is here for womyn” think piece. sexual assault or gen. creepiness bleeds into everything. it shapes how money is allocated. it affects tours and record cycles. it’s not as simple as “tell that dude to cut it out” and it will all get better. currently
column16: my life is good. i love my other job. i’m healthy and happy. financially stable. but
column18: it’s a bummer to think of all the work we’ve missed out on from women because someone was a douchebag (or worse). lifelong dreams deferred. it makes me really sad to think of all the voices that didn’t get included. music we won’t hear. i wish i had an answer
column19: but i don’t. i still feel conflicted at times excusing myself from the race
column20: like it was on me to fix all this. that stops now. it’s not on women
column21: poc or lgbtq to endure others people’s toxic bullshit. do your best
column23: but do not for one second assume just because you were tired of putting up with the status quo that you’re a quitter. how many more people gotta defer their dreams to protect an asshole? love you all. #whyiquitmusic #notaquitter;;en;#metoo

column1: i hope you’re spending it with the one you love the most!

today can be a difficult day for some who feel they have no one to share it with or who are grieving. it’s important to remember that and be sensitive to those experiences when interacting with people today. we all experience the world differently & each day differently and there are some days that are extra polar.
the most important person in your life and the person you should love the most

column2: how can you show love to others?

do something for yourself. can be something small like tidying a corner of your room or something big like buying yourself a flight or booking s trip! maybe book a massage or order dinner. watch that movie you’ve saved on netflix.

column1: if you know someone who might be struggling today
column3: send them a text & show them your love 💕

column4: jobba med och vara fast på samma gård med den som begått ett övergrepp på en. jag har nog aldrig tidigare känt ett sådant hat gentemot en annan människa. och när jag i helgen fick höra att den här killen gjort ett nytt övergrepp på en annan
column5: då nöjde jag mig inte bara med att jag redan skällt ut honom öppet inför alla volontärer och ledare och sagt vad han gjort mot mig. hoppet om att han skulle skämmas så urbota mycket att han aldrig skulle göra det igen
column7: och idag gjorde jag en lång
column8: detaljerad polisanmälan. och jävlar vad skönt det känns. jag hoppas att alla kvinnor där ute står upp för rättigheten till sin egen kropp! för det enda vi verkligen äger i våra liv
column9: det är vår kropp! hashtagen metoo har aldrig betytt så mycket för mig som den gör nu. det är äcklande att ha mött en riktig sexualförbrytare och det är tragiskt men också fruktansvärt tillfredsställande att bryta tystnaden och kanske till och med röra om i grytan i en annan kultur. men jag ska heller aldrig sticka under stolen med att detta varit oerhört påfrestande. jag har både kämpat för mig själv och hjälpt/stöttat min medsyster mycket då hon är från en annan kultur och yngre än jag och tyvärr tog på sig en stor del av skulden till det som hände henne. det var längesedan som jag kämpade så mycket psykiskt som jag har gjort här. det är inte lika lätt att stå upp för sig själv när en är i ett främmande land med ett främmande språk
column11: vänner och internetuppkoppling. och heller aldrig riktigt få nytt syre och ny miljö

column1: 33930;instagram;2019-02-14 17:03:44;FALSE;"good morning and happy valentines day friends! this year has been a year full of growth and learning to love who i'm becoming
column2: and i wanted to share this project i've been working on! this book was meant to re-emphasize that we have to love ourselves first before we can love others; we live in a society where we are always trying to please other people. it was eye-opening for me to learn more about my friends throughout the process of making this and to also learn more about myself. the book will be sold on social media as well as on amazon and 50% of the proceeds will go to the me too movement. i wanted to donate to this movement because they have established a community and a safe haven of advocates and survivors that speak out against sexual violence. especially with social media and dating apps nowadays
column3: we have become prone to superficialities and lost that human-ness in interactions with other people - and so we forget to love. anyways

column2: soul tribe! how are you spending this special day of love ❤️? for me
column3: i’ve chosen to be single for years to really work on my self love. i started dating in high school and had a stream of long term relationships. one right after the other. with no time to heal in between. it’s very similar to being put on auto pilot and that’s really what it felt like
column4: as i look back on it. not very present. one day in my mid 30’s i woke up and i was in a very unhappy marriage
column6: myself or lack of my self
column7: i should say because i didn’t even recognize myself. i didn’t even know who i was anymore. it was the first time
column8: i chose me and i walked away from that life. i knew something had to change within myself and it had to happen at a soul level. i’ve spent years now
column11: healing my mind. it’s been a lot of work and a lot of journeying through the night of the dark soul but so wonderful! where i can wake up on this beautiful day of love and choose to love myself more than i did yesterday! we can never love ourself enough. i choose to be mindful with my inner voice today and moving forward. i choose to smile and laugh today. i choose to love my bulldog
column12: luna more than i loved her yesterday. i also choose to love my soul sisters 👯 more and help them rise up by offering a free virtual webinar tonight called the ascending woman. i choose to have no room in my life for judgement of others
column13: especially my sisters. it’s time to lift each other up on pedestals! when we rise
